DAMATURU – Borno Governor, Professor Babagana Umara Zulum was earlier today in Azare town of Bauchi State in honour of Nigeria’s Minister of Education, Malam Adamu Adamu, who played a key role in establishment of a Federal Polytechnic in Monguno, in line with Zulum’s wish for Borno. The Minister, who sent an invitation to Governor Zulum, gave out his daughter, Barrister Fatima Zarah Adamu in marriage at the Azare Central Mosque on Saturday, January 8, 2022. Zulum joined many dignitaries including the Vice President, Professor Yemi Osinbajo, Senate President Ahmed Lawan, APC National Leader, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, serving Governors that include the host Governor of Bauchi, Sen. Bala Mohammed, APC Caretaker Chairman, Mai Mala Buni of Yobe, and others, former Governors that included Senators Kashim Shettima, Danjuma Goje and others, serving and former Ministers, and Heads of Federal establishments amongst many other leaders.